  <purpose>
    <p> This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of assembly
      relationships. </p>
    <p> This second edition of this part of ISO 10303 incorporates the modifications to the first
      edition listed below. </p>
    <p> The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been modified: </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Assembly_component_relationship;</li>
      <li>Component_upper_level_identification.</li>
    </ul>

    <p> The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been added: </p>
    <ul>
      <li>USE FROM Product_view_definition_arm;</li>
      <li>Product_occurrence_definition_relationship;</li>
      <li>assembly_component_relationship_constraint.</li>
    </ul>
    <p> The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been removed: </p>
    <ul>
      <li>USE FROM Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.</li>
    </ul>
    <p> In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, the MIM schema and
      the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM. </p>
  </purpose>

  <inscope>
    <li>specification of the use of a product version as a component of an assembly;</li>
    <li>specification of a parent-child assembly relationship;</li>
    <li>identification of a component of an assembly with respect to an upper level in the assembly
      structure;</li>
    <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref
        linkend="product_view_definition:1_scope">Product view definition</module_ref>, ISO/TS
      10303-1019;</li>
    <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="value_with_unit:1_scope"
        >Value with unit</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1054.</li>
  </inscope>

  <outscope>
    <li>characterization of the position of a component in an assembly; <note>This aspect is
        specified in the Contextual shape positioning module.</note>
    </li>
    <li>characterization of a component quantity with a qualified quantity or a quantity range.</li>
  </outscope>
